							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/adamkuper/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Adam-Kuper-e1712587668370-100x100.jpeg" width="100" height="100" alt="Adam Kuper" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/adamkuper/">Adam Kuper</a></h6>
										Adam Kuper is a fellow of the British Academy and a recipient of the Royal Anthropological Institute’s Huxley Memorial Medal. He was Centennial Professor of Anthropology at the London School of Economics and a visiting professor at Boston University. He has appeared often on BBC TV and radio, and he regularly reviews for <em>The London Review of Books</em>, <em>The Times Literary Supplement</em> and the <em>Wall Street Journal</em>.																			</div>
